%N A389320 Upper (3/4)-midsequence of square numbers and negative triangular numbers; see Comments.
%C A389320 Suppose that s = (s(n)) and t = (t(n)) are sequences of numbers and r > 0. The lower (r)-midsequence of s and t is given by u = floor(r*(s + t)); the upper r-midsequence of s and t is given by v = ceiling(r*(s + t)). If s and t are linearly recurrent and r is rational, then u and v are linearly recurrent.
%H A389320 <a href="/index/Rec#order_09">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (3,-4,4,-4,4,-4,4,-3,1).
%F A389320 a(n) = ceiling((3/8)*(n^2 - n)).
%F A389320 a(n) = 3*a(n-1) - 4*a(n-2) + 4*a(n-3) - 4*a(n-4) + 4*a(n-5) - 4*a(n-6) + 4*a(n-7) - 3*a(n-8) + a(n-9), with (a(0),...,a(8)) = (0, 0, 1, 3, 5, 8, 12, 16, 21).
%e A389320 s = (n^2) = A000290 = (0, 1, 4, 9, 16, 25, ...).
%e A389320 t = -(n*(n+1)/2) = -A000217 = (0, -1, -3, -6, -10, -15, ...).
%e A389320 u(n) = floor((3/4)*(0-0, 1-1, 4-3, 9-6, 16-10, ...)) = (0, 0, 0, 2, 4, 7, 11, 15, ...).
%e A389320 v(n) = ceiling((3/4)*(0-0, 1-1, 4-3, 9-6, 16-10, ...)) = (0, 0, 1, 3, 5, 8, 12, 16, ...).
%t A389320 s[n_] := n^2; t[n_] := - n (n + 1)/2; r = 3/4;
%t A389320 u[n_] := Floor[r*(s[n] + t[n])];
%t A389320 v[n_] := Ceiling[r*(s[n] + t[n])];
%t A389320 Table[u[n], {n, 0, 60}]  (* A389319 *)
%t A389320 Table[v[n], {n, 0, 60}]  (* A389320 *)
%o A389320 (Python)
%o A389320 def A389320(n): return (3*n*(n-1)-1>>3)+1 # _Chai Wah Wu_, Nov 08 2025
